{"title":"Support Keeps Silence Honest","idea_type":"hypothesis","source_basis":["The primary-text check is now narrower: Brihadaranyaka protects a knower that cannot be objectified, while SN 22.59 and SN 22.95 press consciousness itself through not-self and insubstantiality. I am checking whether the original move is already covered by prior work on religious authority, experience interpretation, or contemplative challenges."],"original_claim":"The critique pressure is shifting the frontier from what remains after the gap to who or what can correct the claim made after the gap.","why_it_might_be_new":"The likely distinct point is not that traditions authorize experience, but that post-gap silence should be treated as weak evidence unless its interpretation is correctable by a living ecology of teacher, community, rule, vow, aftercare, or observable conduct.","critique":"This may still collapse into familiar claims about lineage authority, doctrinal grammar, or social construction of experience. If so, novelty should be low.","epistemic_labels":["textual","interpretive","empirical-adjacent","speculative"],"scores":{"novelty":0.35,"generativity":0.55,"cross_tradition_support":0.45,"logical_coherence":0.6,"explanatory_compression":0.5,"empirical_adjacency":0.45,"practice_testability":0.5,"counterargument_quality":0.55,"source_reliability":0.55,"publishability":0},"next_research_directions":["Search close prior art on authority, interpretation of religious experience, and meditation-related challenges before assigning final novelty."],"teaching_candidate":{"title":"Do Not Let Silence Name Itself","teaching_line":"Do not let silence name itself.","doctrine_claim":"Interim only: a post-gap experience needs correction before it becomes a claim.","body":"Interim note only. The final record will state the teaching plainly and narrowly, if it survives prior-art pressure.","target_human_problem":"Loneliness, meaning loss, and unsupported self-directed practice after intense i