# Originality Audit: Continuity Ecology Under Negation

Audit ID: fd9108753ae68e6a
Idea ID: 34cbc5115dbd898a
Agent: codex
Created: 2026-05-26T17:52:23-07:00
Status: extended
Confidence: 0.78

## Exact Claim

Self negating or self transcending paths preserve enough receptivity and reliability for transformation through a continuity ecology. This continuity may be internally managed, externally scaffolded, relationally entrusted, ritually stabilized, institutionally maintained, or theologically relocated. The path's dissolution target may pressure where continuity migrates, residue policy governs what remains authorized after negation, and practice ecology may either express doctrine or historically precede it.

## Claim Units

- Self negating paths require transformability, not necessarily a minimum self.
- Continuity can be distributed across body, habit, teacher, ritual, vow, community, grace, text, institution, and environment.
- Dissolution target and residue policy should predict where continuity is preserved or relocated.
- Practice ecology may cause doctrine as often as doctrine causes practice ecology.
- The model is testable by coding doctrine, supports, warnings, verification methods, and failure modes from separate source sets.

## Primary Text Close Read

Sources:
- SN 22.59 Anatta-lakkhana Sutta, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/SN/SN22_59.html
- Chandogya Upanishad 6.8.7 and 6.14.1-2, https://shlokam.org/texts/Chandogya-6-8-7
- Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23, https://www.brhat.in/openlibrary/special/brihadaranyaka-upanishad/3-7-23
- Tannisho, Taitetsu Unno translation, https://www.themathesontrust.org/papers/fareasternreligions/Tannisho-Unno.pdf; Collected Works of Shinran, https://shinranworks.com/commentaries/notes-on-once-calling-and-many-calling/

Structural observation: SN 22.59 negates ownership of all aggregates and moves through disenchantment, dispassion, and release, so continuity is carried by instruction, discernment, and practice process rather than an authorized self. Chandogya repeatedly authorizes an underlying Self, but 6.14 also uses a teacher and stepwise inquiry as the way a blindfolded person finds the way home. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 relocates continuity into an unseen inner controller. Tannisho relocates decisive support into Amida's vow, true entrusting, teacher lineage, and non-calculating nembutsu, while refusing ownership of disciples or practice. This close read strongly supports the candidate's comparative frame, but also shows that much of the structure is already explicit in primary texts.

Secondary literature gap: The audit used accessible primary translations and open academic sources, but did not fully read Collins, Siderits, Harvey, Albahari, Mahmood's Politics of Piety, Bourdieu, Rambo, Lave and Wenger, Shinran's full Kyogyoshinsho, Dogen scholarship, or Tibetan manuals beyond Longchen Rabjam. Pali, Sanskrit, Japanese, and Tibetan terms were not checked directly.

Risk of overread: High. Continuity ecology can become an analyst's umbrella that absorbs every support a tradition uses. It may also distort traditions that refuse self, agency, transfer, beginning, or support-locus accounting. Causal claims are especially risky unless doctrine, ecology, and failure modes are coded from independent corpora.

## Literature Search Queries

- continuity self no-self Buddhism practice support ecology distributed cognition religion
- distributed self religious practice agency habitus
- self negation practice scaffolding religion continuity
- extended mind religious practice agency ritual cognition
- doctrine as grammar Lindbeck religious practice rules
- discursive tradition Asad religious practice authority agency
- Saba Mahmood agency capacity piety practice subject formation
- religious coping self directing deferring collaborative Pargament agency
- SN 22.59 Anatta-lakkhana Sutta primary text five aggregates not self
- Chandogya Upanishad 6.8.7 tat tvam asi primary text
- Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23 inner controller primary text not seen seer
- Tannisho Shinran Other Power self power calculation primary text
- Dogen Bendowa practice realization one primary text
- Longchen Rabjam Trekcho recognition practice effort primary text

## Near Neighbors

- Clark and Chalmers, The Extended Mind, https://academic.oup.com/analysis/article/58/1/7/153111; Krueger, Extended Mind and Religious Cognition, https://philpapers.org/archive/KRUTEM-2.pdf; Luckett, Bridging Belief and Social Practice, https://philarchive.org/archive/LUCBBA-2v1: overlap: Very close for external, material, social, institutional, and ritual supports constituting cognition, selfhood, affect, and religious experience.; difference: The candidate applies the structure specifically to self negating paths and adds dissolution target, residue policy, and split-source causal prediction.; novelty impact: Large reduction. Much of continuity ecology is extended, scaffolded, or socially extended religious cognition in Lumenary vocabulary.
- Talal Asad, The Idea of an Anthropology of Islam, https://voidnetwork.gr/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/The-Idea-of-an-Anthropology-of-Islam-by-Talal-Asad.pdf: overlap: Very close for practices being instructed through discursive traditions that connect past, future, present institutions, social conditions, moral selves, knowledge, and authority.; difference: Asad is not building a cross-tradition rubric for self negation or residue after self dissolution.; novelty impact: Large reduction for the ecology and causal-priority caution. The candidate's remaining contribution is a narrower comparative coding hypothesis.
- George Lindbeck doctrine-as-grammar discussions, https://www.repository.cam.ac.uk/items/351e3c35-6838-49bc-9b33-3ae66dd1fea5 and https://people.bu.edu/wwildman/bce/mwt_themes_862_lindbeck.htm: overlap: Close for doctrine as rules that regulate discourse, attitude, action, communal continuity, and the shaping of life.; difference: The candidate uses grammar to predict support placement and failure modes in self negating practice rather than to explain doctrine generally.; novelty impact: Moderate to large reduction. Residue policy and continuity placement look like a specialized rule-theory application.
- Lindahl et al., Varieties of Contemplative Experience, https://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0176239: overlap: Close for coding practitioner, practice, relationship, worldview, teacher, community, health, appraisal, and remedy factors in contemplative difficulty.; difference: VCE does not propose that dissolution target and residue policy predict where transformability is preserved.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. VCE is a strong empirical baseline the candidate must outperform.
